<DOC><DOCNO> AP891221-0255 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-21-89 2304EST</FILEID><FIRST>s f BC-Eastern-Chronology Adv24   12-21 0637</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Eastern-Chronology, Adv 24,0668</SECOND><HEAD>$adv24</HEAD><HEAD>For release Sunday, Dec. 24</HEAD><HEAD>With BC-Eastern-Then and Now</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Here are key events in the Machinists union strike againstEastern Airlines:   _March 3 _ President Bush refuses National Mediation Boardrequest to use his authority under Railway Labor Act to delaystrike 60 days. Machinists reject Eastern's latest contract offer.Talks collapse at midnight.   _March 4 _ Strike begins, canceling almost 90 percent of Easternflights, stranding passengers across nation, in Caribbean and LatinAmerica.   _March 5 _ Few Eastern flights take off as pilots honor thestrike.   _March 6 _ Eastern idles 7,000 non-union workers and cancelsnearly all flights. Airline asks federal judge to order pilots backto work.   _March 7 _ Judge refuses to order pilots back to work. Easternfurloughs another 2,500 employees.   _March 9 _ Eastern files for protection from creditors underChapter 11 in U.S. Bankruptcy Court in New York.   _March 31 _ Real estate tycoon Donald Trump announces he hascompleted a restructured deal to buy Eastern's Northeast shuttleservice for $365 million. The new deal, revised from an October1988 agreement, provides him with four additional Boeing 727s.   _April 6 _ A group led by former baseball commissioner Peter V.Ueberroth announces it will acquire Eastern and a 19.9 percentstake in the System One reservations system in a deal valued at$464 million. Under the deal with Eastern's parent Texas Air Corp.,Eastern employees would own 30 percent of the airline in return forwage and benefit concessions.   _April 12 _ Ueberroth and Eastern announce the buyout proposalhas collapsed. Eastern says it intends to reorganize as a smallercarrier serving roughly 50 percent to 60 percent of its pre-strikeschedule.   _May 3 _ A group led by William Howard, former chairman ofPiedmont Aviation, discloses that it is interested in making abuyout proposal for all of Eastern. Chicago businessman JosephRitchie already has expressed interest.   America West Airlines offers to pay $726 million for Eastern'sshuttle and 10 Boeing 757s.   _May 23 _ Eastern graduates its first class of new pilots hiredsince the start of the strike.   _May 25 _ Lifland formally approves the sale of the shuttle toTrump for $365 million, after America West withdraws offer becauseof failure to arrange financing.   _June 1 _ David Shapiro, bankruptcy examiner in the Easterncase, dismisses the Howard group's offer.   _June 2 _ Eastern announces an austerity program for non-unionemployees.   _June 5 _ Lifland removes the Ritchie plan from consideration.   _July 21 _ Eastern submits a reorganization plan to thebankruptcy court. Creditors express approval.   _Early August _ The striking pilots vote to continue theirsympathy walkout.   _Aug. 24 _ Texas Air Chairman Frank Lorenzo says he isconsidering selling all or part of Continental Airlines, Eastern'ssister carrier. Scandinavian Airlines Systems, which owns 9.9percent of Texas Air, reportedly is interested in buying a stake inContinental.   _Aug. 31 _ Eastern abandons an earlier plan to sell LatinAmerican routes, giving it around $370 million less in cash byyearend than first projected.   _Sept. 8 _ The striking pilots vote to throw out their leader,Jack Bavis, for proposing that they consider ending walkout.   _Sept. 13 _ Lorenzo tells Texas Air shareholders Eastern willturn a profit in 1990. SAS says it has no ``immediate interest'' inbuying part of Continental.   _Nov. 22 _ The 2,250 pilots still on strike vote to end it. Thestriking flight attendants quickly follow, leaving the Machinistsalone on picket lines. Eastern says few jobs are left because it'shired replacements.   _Dec. 19 _ American Airlines announces it will buy LatinAmerican routes and other assets from Texas Air for $471 million.The deal shrinks Eastern to about two-thirds its pre-strike size.</TEXT><NOTE>End Adv Sunday, Dec. 24</NOTE></DOC>